{
  "local_port": 39062,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "Linking your Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account can be done through several methods. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide for each method:\n\n### 1. **Linking via Internet Banking:**\n   - **Log in** to your SBI Internet Banking account.\n   - Navigate to the **\u201cProfile\u201d** section.\n   - Click on **\u201cLink Aadhaar\u201d**.\n   - Enter your **Aadhaar Number** and other required details.\n   - Confirm the details and click on the **\u201cSubmit\u201d** button.\n   - You will receive a confirmation message regarding the status of your request.\n\n### 2. **Using SBI Mobile App:**\n   - Open the **SBI YONO app** on your smartphone.\n   - Log in using your credentials.\n   - Go to the **\u201cHome\u201d** screen and select the **\u201cServices\u201d** tab.\n   - Choose **\u201cUpdate Aadhaar\u201d** or **\u201cLink Aadhaar\u201d**.\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number and submit.\n   - Wait for an OTP on your registered mobile number to complete the process.\n\n### 3. **Linking via SMS:**\n   - You can also link your Aadhaar by sending an SMS from your registered mobile number.\n   - Send an SMS in the following format: \n     ```\n     LINK<space>Aadhaar Number<space>Account Number\n     ```\n   - Send this SMS to the number **567676**. You will receive a confirmation SMS once your Aadhaar is linked.\n\n### 4. **Linking at SBI Branch:**\n   - Visit your nearest SBI branch.\n   - Carry your valid Aadhaar card and passbook or account details.\n   - Fill out the Aadhaar linking form provided by the bank.\n   - Submit the form along with a photocopy of your Aadhaar card.\n   - You will receive a receipt or acknowledgment once the request is processed.\n\n### 5. **Linking through ATM:**\n   - Visit an SBI ATM.\n   - Insert your debit card and enter your PIN.\n   - Select the option for **\u201cAadhaar Linking\u201d** (if available).\n   - Follow the prompts to enter your Aadhaar number and complete the process.\n\n### **Important Notes:**\n- Ensure that your mobile number linked with the Aadhaar card is active, as you will receive OTPs and confirmation messages.\n- The process might take a few hours to a couple of days for the linking to be completed.\n- You can check your Aadhaar linking status using the SBI website or by visiting the bank.\n\nMake sure to keep your documents handy and follow the instructions carefully. If you face any issues, it\u2019s advisable to contact SBI customer service for assistance.",
